Reasoning: The paper deals with the achievable degrees of freedom in a wireless network, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The network consists of communication nodes and relay nodes, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed technique for relay node selection is distributed and opportunistic, which is related to control and optimization (cs.SY). The simulations involve measuring achievable rates, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the proposed technique, which is related to computer engineering (cs.CE).
